<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFSteve_Appleford">Steve Appleford (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2004-09-26"><a href="/wiki/2004" title="2004">2004</a>-<a href="/wiki/September_26" title="September 26">09-26</a></span>). <a href="http://www.lacitybeat.com/article.php?id=5412&amp;IssueNum=203" class="external text" title="http://www.lacitybeat.com/article.php?id=5412&amp;IssueNum=203" rel="nofollow">"The Past, the Present &amp; the Future"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Los_Angeles_CityBeat" title="Los Angeles CityBeat" class="mw-redirect">Los Angeles CityBeat</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.lacitybeat.com/article.php?id=5412&amp;IssueNum=203" class="external free" title="http://www.lacitybeat.com/article.php?id=5412&amp;IssueNum=203" rel="nofollow">http://www.lacitybeat.com/article.php?id=5412&amp;IssueNum=203</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-05-11</span>.  "Critics have called <i>The Good, the Bad &amp; the Queen</i> (Virgin) a “headphones record,” which is one way of pointing to the layers of sound and subtlety within its grooves."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Past%2C+the+Present+%26+the+Future&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Steve+Appleford&amp;rft.au=Steve+Appleford&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2004-09-26%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BLos+Angeles+CityBeat%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lacitybeat.com%2Farticle.php%3Fid%3D5412%26IssueNum%3D203&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Headphones"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.osha.gov/SLTC/etools/computerworkstations/checklist.html" class="external text" title="http://www.osha.gov/SLTC/etools/computerworkstations/checklist.html" rel="nofollow">United States Department of Labor. Occupational Safety &amp; Health Administration. <i>Computer Workstation. Checklist.</i></a> Accessed February 2, 2009.</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.asha.org/public/hearing/disorders/causes_adults.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.asha.org/public/hearing/disorders/causes_adults.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.asha.org/public/hearing/disorders/causes_adults.htm</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.nidcd.nih.gov/health/hearing/noise.asp" class="external free" title="http://www.nidcd.nih.gov/health/hearing/noise.asp" rel="nofollow">http://www.nidcd.nih.gov/health/hearing/noise.asp</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.audiologyonline.com/articles/article_detail.asp?article_id=221" class="external free" title="http://www.audiologyonline.com/articles/article_detail.asp?article_id=221" rel="nofollow">http://www.audiologyonline.com/articles/article_detail.asp?article_id=221</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.headwize.com/articles/hearing_art.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.headwize.com/articles/hearing_art.htm" rel="nofollow">Headwize.com. <i>Preventing Hearing Damage When Listening With Headphones</i></a></li>
</ol>
</div>
